22/09/2003
SINAIA, Romania -- During a meeting on Sunday (21 September), the justice ministers of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Greece, Macedonia, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro agreed on the creation of a regional network for legal co-operation against crime.
In a joint statement, the ministers reiterated their countries' commitment to preventing and combating organised crime as well as to strengthening the principles of domestic and international law.
They also announced the establishment of a permanent co-operation network, which would enhance contacts among the magistrates and justice ministries of states in the region and bolster progress in the EU integration process.
(Rompres - 22/09/03)
